		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Looks great!  Good job getting everything together and fully announced.<br /><br />A few minor comments, do with them as you please.<br /><br />Registration: I'd recommend explaining that it's non-obligatory, and can be done at any point.  There is no deadline to register afaik, just a good idea to do it sooner vice later if you're thinking about making a submission so you can stay in the loop.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Use of existing tools/libraries/code qualify as long as permission has been granted by the author.</div>What about open source, openly shared code?  So long as licensing requirements are upheld, would it not be okay to use especially things like generic libraries and such?  Or if someone took a hello world example, or nerdy nights tutorial do we want to discourage things like that?

		

		</td>
